What you need to know:

In the 1970s and 80s, Patel’s company was a constant feature in  the Ministry of Health tenders for drugs.Dr Patel knew his way around the Ministry of Health and at the Central Medical Stores, now known as Kemsa.There have been attempts to right the wrongs in the medical supply chain.After the Covid-19 pandemic emerged, the suppliers, both old and young, looked at Kemsa as their cash cow. 